# PRISM — environment configuration example
# =============================================================================
# Copy to `.env` and edit, OR export these directly in your shell / systemd
# unit / launchd plist. `start.sh` already sets sensible defaults for the
# local-dev and --https paths, so a bare `./start.sh` works without any of
# this. Production deployments should set every variable in the "required"
# block below and review every flag in the "security" block.
#
# Loading: PRISM does NOT auto-load `.env`. Either `source .env` in your
# shell before running, or use `env $(cat .env | xargs) python app.py`, or
# set these through your process manager. Keeping loading explicit avoids
# the "which config is actually live?" confusion every Flask project hits
# by month three.
#
# Convention: every PRISM-specific flag is prefixed `LAB_SCHEDULER_`. Third-
# party knobs (SMTP_*, OWNER_EMAILS) keep their conventional names.
# =============================================================================


# -- REQUIRED in production ---------------------------------------------------

# Flask session signing key. `start.sh` auto-generates one per launch via
# `openssl rand -hex 32`; set it explicitly in production so sessions
# survive a restart. 32+ random bytes, hex or base64.
LAB_SCHEDULER_SECRET_KEY=change-me-to-32-random-bytes

# Comma-separated list of super-admin emails. These accounts bypass every
# RBAC gate and can access `/admin/*` unconditionally. Keep it short.
OWNER_EMAILS=admin@lab.local


# -- SECURITY flags (review every one before going to production) ------------

# Set 1/true to enforce HTTPS-only session cookies. `start.sh --https`
# sets this automatically. Leaving it blank allows plain-HTTP sessions,
# which is fine only for localhost dev.
LAB_SCHEDULER_COOKIE_SECURE=

# Set 1/true to enable Flask-WTF CSRF enforcement. Every POST form must
# then carry a `csrf_token` hidden input. Currently OFF by default until
# W6.11 rolls the tokens into all ~30 forms and the three regression
# test scripts. Flip to 1 after W6.11 lands.
LAB_SCHEDULER_CSRF=

# `start.sh --https` sets this to `true` and launches app.py with a
# self-signed cert from `certs/`. No effect if set without --https.
LAB_SCHEDULER_HTTPS=

# Set 1 to enable Flask's debug reloader and verbose tracebacks. NEVER
# turn this on in production — it exposes an interactive Python console
# on the 500 page. `start.sh` sets it to 0 under --https and 1 otherwise.
LAB_SCHEDULER_DEBUG=0


# -- DEMO MODE (LAN demo / workshop deployments) ------------------------------

# Gates `/demo/switch` (one-click user switcher) and the `seed_data()`
# bootstrap on first boot. Default 1 so `./start.sh` gives a populated
# demo DB out of the box. Set 0 in production to lock both paths down.
LAB_SCHEDULER_DEMO_MODE=1


# -- SMTP (optional, used by invite + password-reset emails) ------------------

# If your lab has an internal relay, point these at it. Default is
# `localhost:25` which fails silently on most machines — that's fine
# for dev, not for production.
SMTP_HOST=localhost
SMTP_PORT=25


# -- CRAWLERS (test / CI knobs, not read by app.py) ---------------------------

# Random-walk step count for `crawlers/strategies/random_walk.py`.
# Coupon-collector math: 800 steps ~= 95% coverage of the 128
# (role x route) cells, 1000 steps plateaus at ~99%. Bump to 2000 only
# when chasing a specific intermittent 5xx.
CRAWLER_RANDOM_WALK_STEPS=800

# Temp SQLite path used by `crawlers/harness.py` and the `test_*_crawl.py`
# scripts. App.py does NOT read this — it uses `BASE_DIR/lab_scheduler.db`
# unconditionally. Documented here so agents reading the env surface
# don't assume it controls the live DB.
# LAB_SCHEDULER_DB_PATH=/tmp/prism-test.db


# -- ERP MODULE SYSTEM --------------------------------------------------------
# Comma-separated list of enabled ERP modules. Default: ALL modules on.
# Set this to ship a deployment with only the modules the customer needs.
#
# Available modules:
#   instruments   — Instrument Portal (list, detail, form control, custom fields)
#   finance       — Finance Portal (grants, budgets, invoices, payments)
#   inbox         — Email / Inbox System (reply, attach, folders)
#   notifications — Notification System (broadcast notices, noticeboard)
#   attendance    — Attendance Portal
#   queue         — Queue / Schedule (request workflow, bulk actions)
#   calendar      — Calendar views
#   stats         — Statistics / Analytics
#   admin         — Admin panels (user management, dev panel)
#
# Examples:
#   PRISM_MODULES=instruments,finance,inbox           # lab facility + billing
#   PRISM_MODULES=attendance,inbox,notifications      # HR / personnel only
#   PRISM_MODULES=instruments,queue,inbox              # lean lab, no finance
#
# Omit this line entirely (or leave blank) to enable everything:
# PRISM_MODULES=


# -- SERVER PORT ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Default: 5055. Change if the port is already in use.
# LAB_SCHEDULER_PORT=5055
